-- Calpers Commodity Holdings Declined 5.5% in April to $1.214B
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 2013-06-17T14:26:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-17/calpers-commodity-holdings-declined-5-5-in-april-to-1-214b.html
The California Public Employees’
Retirement System, the largest U.S. pension fund, reported the
value of its commodity holdings fell 5.5 percent in April from
the previous month.  The fund held $1.214 billion in commodities as of April 30,
the most-recent data available, or 0.5 percent of the total
assets listed at $263.944 billion, according to a monthly  report 
posted on the fund’s website for today’s investment committee
 meeting . That’s down from $1.284 billion on  March 31 , or 0.5
percent of total assets of $257.395 billion.  Commodities were the worst-performing asset class in the
portfolio during the 12 months through April, dropping 9.8
percent, according to the report. All other asset groups
increased, with a total fund return of 13.4 percent.  The fund’s board is meeting today, tomorrow and June 19,
according to the Calpers  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
